# Java script executor method and operation:
OPERATIONS POSSIBLE WITH JAVASCRIPT EXECUTOR (NOT RELIABLE WITH NORMAL SELENIUM)
✅ 1. Click Hidden / Covered Elements

Selenium may throw:

ElementClickInterceptedException

JS ignores visibility rules.

element = driver.find_element(By.ID, "submitBtn")
driver.execute_script("arguments[0].click();", element)


✔ Works even if:

Element is hidden behind another element

CSS overlay present

Element is off-screen

✅ 2. Enter Text Without send_keys()
input_box = driver.find_element(By.ID, "email")
driver.execute_script("arguments[0].value='test@mail.com';", input_box)


Useful when:

Input field blocks typing

Key events are restricted

✅ 3. Scroll Page / Element (Precise Control)
Scroll to bottom
driver.execute_script("window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);")

Scroll to element
element = driver.find_element(By.ID, "footer")
driver.execute_script("arguments[0].scrollIntoView(true);", element)

✅ 4. Remove Disabled Attribute
button = driver.find_element(By.ID, "payBtn")
driver.execute_script("arguments[0].removeAttribute('disabled');", button)


Now Selenium can click it.

✅ 5. Modify CSS (Make Hidden Element Visible)
element = driver.find_element(By.ID, "hiddenDiv")
driver.execute_script("arguments[0].style.display='block';", element)

✅ 6. Get Page Title / URL via JS
title = driver.execute_script("return document.title;")
url = driver.execute_script("return document.URL;")

✅ 7. Get Hidden Text or Inner HTML
text = driver.execute_script("return arguments[0].innerText;", element)
html = driver.execute_script("return arguments[0].innerHTML;", element)

✅ 8. Highlight Element (For Debugging)
driver.execute_script("arguments[0].style.border='3px solid red'", element)

✅ 9. Handle Date Picker Directly
date = driver.find_element(By.ID, "dateField")
driver.execute_script("arguments[0].value='2026-01-27';", date)

✅ 10. Trigger Browser Alert
driver.execute_script("alert('Test Alert');")

✅ 11. Refresh Page Without Selenium Command
driver.execute_script("location.reload();")

✅ 12. Navigate Back/Forward
driver.execute_script("window.history.back();")
driver.execute_script("window.history.forward();")

✅ 13. Click Using Coordinates
driver.execute_script("""
var evt = document.createEvent('MouseEvents');
evt.initMouseEvent('click',true,true,window,0,0,0,100,200,false,false,false,false,0,null);
document.elementFromPoint(100,200).dispatchEvent(evt);
""")

✅ 14. Work with Shadow DOM (Very Important)

Selenium struggles with Shadow DOM.

shadow_host = driver.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "custom-element")
shadow_root = driver.execute_script("return arguments[0].shadowRoot", shadow_host)
element = shadow_root.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "button")
element.click()

✅ 15. Count Elements Faster
count = driver.execute_script("return document.getElementsByTagName('a').length;")

✅ 16. Zoom In / Zoom Out
driver.execute_script("document.body.style.zoom='80%'")

✅ 17. Check if Page Fully Loaded
state = driver.execute_script("return document.readyState;")